SOUTH CANTEEN FOOD STALL ORDERING SYSTEM
Python Programming Project - Task Kill List
EG1P12 - Programming | Effective Date: 20 Apr 2026
==================================================

PROJECT SUMMARY
--------------------------------------------------
A new food stall at South Canteen wants a user-friendly
online ordering system. Build a Python program that lets
customers browse the menu, place orders, review/edit them,
apply NYP student/staff discounts, and print a final
itemised receipt.


CODEBASE KILL LIST
==================================================

1. MENU SYSTEM
--------------------------------------------------
[✔ ] Store menu items in a data structure (dict or list of dicts) - name, price, category
[✔ ] Function to display the menu in a clean, numbered format

2. ORDERING FLOW
--------------------------------------------------
[✔ ] Function to let customer select item(s) + enter quantity
[✔ ] Support ordering multiple items within a single transaction (loop until customer says they're done)
[✔ ] Store the running order (e.g. list of dicts: item, qty, price)

3. REVIEW / EDIT ORDER
--------------------------------------------------
[✔ ] Function to display the current order so far
[✔ ] Let customer change quantity or remove an item before finalising

4. DISCOUNT LOGIC
--------------------------------------------------
[ ] Ask customer if they are an NYP student, NYP staff, or neither
[ ] Apply 10% discount (student) or 5% discount (staff)
[ ] Dedicated function to calculate discount cleanly

5. BILL CALCULATION
--------------------------------------------------
[ ] Subtotal -> apply discount -> final payable amount
[ ] Function to calculate total, separate from display logic

6. RECEIPT / OUTPUT
--------------------------------------------------
[ ] Print a clean, organised receipt: items, qty, price each, subtotal, discount applied, final total
[ ] Formatting matters here - this is a direct rubric point (accuracy & presentation)

7. MAIN PROGRAM LOOP
--------------------------------------------------
[ ] Keep running until customer indicates they're finished ordering
[ ] Input validation everywhere - no crashing on bad input (letters in number fields, invalid item numbers, etc.)

8. CREATIVE FEATURE (Rubric IV)
--------------------------------------------------
[ ] Pick one enhancement once the core program works, e.g.:
    [ ] Add-on items (saw "Add On" options in the menu photo)
    [ ] Order history / receipt saved to a .txt file
    [ ] Timestamp on receipt
    [ ] Simple ASCII-art header for branding


